			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Slots<a name="69515"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 11 04 12:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>How do they &quot;work&quot;?  That's a pretty generic question...not sure exactly what you're asking, or what your EQ experience is, so forgive me if this is a newbie answer.
<br />

<br />
Augment slots are a way to customize your gear with an extra stat buff (+STA, +regen, +vsMagic, etc) of your choosing.  Some mobs drop an &quot;augment stone&quot; (hereafter referred to as &quot;augs&quot; ) that you can loot (no drop on the blue servers) and add to a piece of your gear at any of the Wayfarer camps.  The augs drop in LDoN adventures (and the uber-level zones) or can be purchased with Adventure Points from the merchants at the Wayfarer camps.
<br />

<br />
The augs have restrictions on which pieces of gear they can be added to.  All gear has various &quot;Slots&quot; available, classified by what kind of augs can be added to it.  Most have at least one &quot;Type 7&quot; slot which can be filled by a Type 7 aug or a &quot;fits in any slot&quot; aug, assuming the aug doesn't have a restriction on which slot the gear is worn in (some augs can only be fitted to chest, or head, or wrist, etc, pieces).  
<br />

<br />
Some of the LDoN-purchased gear have multiple slots available, allowing you to add several different augs.  You basically have to match the aug's &quot;Slot Type&quot; (Type 3, Type 1, etc) to the available slots in the gear.  Augs that say &quot;fits in any slot type&quot; do exactly that, obviously.
<br />

<br />
Does that answer the question?
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
