				<td colspan="2"><span>I think Areo has it pretty accurate if you substitute the word 'type' for 'slot'.  As example a piece of armor bought from the ldon merchant can have
<br />
slot 1 = type 1
<br />
slot 2 = type 2
<br />
slot 3 = type 3
<br />
and this is what most of them have.  But some of the cheaper pieces will have
<br />
slot 1 = type 1
<br />
slot 2 = type 1
<br />
slot 3 = type 2
<br />
It is the type # that tells you what aug can go in it.</span></td>
